Package com.intellij.openapi.util

Class MultiValuesMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.openapi.util.MultiValuesMap<K,V>
  • Deprecated. 
    use MultiMap directly.

    On migration please note that MultiMap has few differences:
    • MultiMap.get(Object) method returns non-null value. In case there is no value for the key - empty collection is returned.
    • MultiMap.values method returns a real values collection, not a copy. Be careful with modifications.
    • Default implementations of MultiMap may not permit null keys and/or null values
